{"source_hash": "79417741219c4584", "candidate": {"id": "cand-015", "name": "Sienna Park", "raw_cv": "SIENNA PARK\nsienna.park@email.com | Remote (Bristol, UK)\n\nSENIOR PRODUCT MANAGER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nProduct manager with 7 years of experience in B2B SaaS and impact tech. Strong track record in enterprise workflow products and purpose-driven organisations. Experienced people manager with 3 direct reports. Deeply committed to ethical, sustainable business practices.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nSenior Product Manager \u2014 Provenance (Remote) (2021\u2013present)\n- Led the supply chain transparency product, helping brands communicate sustainability credentials to consumers\n- Managed a team of 3 PMs and collaborated across engineering, design, and customer success\n- Grew the brand-facing product from 40 to 200 paying customers in 2 years\n\nProduct Manager \u2014 Biosite Systems, Bristol (2018\u20132021)\n- PM for workforce management and compliance tracking product\n- Led implementation of a GDPR compliance module used by 300+ construction sites\n\nAssociate PM \u2014 Brightpearl (now Sage), Bristol (2017\u20132018)\n\nSKILLS\nProduct strategy, roadmapping, user research, B2B SaaS, SQL (basic), Amplitude, Jira, Figma, sustainability domain knowledge, people management\n\nEDUCATION\nBA Philosophy, Politics and Economics \u2014 University of Oxford (2014\u20132017)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen", "raw_linkedin": "Product leader working at the intersection of B2B SaaS and sustainability. Seven years in product management, currently leading the supply chain transparency product at Provenance \u2014 helping some of the world's most ambitious brands prove their ESG claims with real data. I manage a small PM team and thrive in mission-driven environments. Fully remote and proud of it. I care deeply about the purpose behind the work \u2014 not just the product metrics.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Sienna, tell me about your experience managing a PM team.\n\nSienna: At Provenance I've had three direct reports for two years. I run weekly 1:1s, monthly team OKR reviews, and quarterly career development conversations. I've promoted one associate PM to PM in that time. I find people management one of the most rewarding parts of the role.\n\nInterviewer: And the domain fit. We're a procurement workflow SaaS company \u2014 how does your sustainability background map to that?\n\nSienna: Supply chain and procurement are deeply linked to sustainability. I understand procurement workflows from the supplier-transparency angle \u2014 I've spent years thinking about how procurement teams make sourcing decisions. I think I'd bring a unique perspective on supplier relationships that most PM candidates wouldn't have.\n\nInterviewer: We're a fully remote, async-first company. That works for you?\n\nSienna: Perfectly. I've been fully remote since 2019 and I advocate strongly for it.\n\nInterviewer: I need to ask about something from your LinkedIn profile \u2014 you mention being committed to ethical business. Is that just values-level, or does it affect the companies you'd consider working for?\n\nSienna: That's an important question and I'll be honest with you. I do have a strong preference for working with B-corp certified companies or companies on a clear certification pathway. It matters to me at a deep level. CloudBridge isn't B-corp certified as far as I know. I'd want to understand the company's position on sustainability and whether certification is something you're working toward, before I'd feel fully committed to joining.\n\nInterviewer: We're not currently pursuing B-corp certification. We take ethics seriously, but it's not a formal commitment.\n\nSienna: I see. I'd want to sit with that. It's not an automatic dealbreaker, but it's a significant consideration for me.", "years_experience": 7.0, "skills": ["Product strategy", "Roadmapping", "User research", "B2B SaaS", "SQL", "Amplitude", "Jira", "Figma", "Sustainability domain knowledge", "People management", "Supply chain transparency", "Enterprise workflow products", "GDPR compliance", "Team leadership", "OKR planning", "Career development coaching"], "industries": ["B2B SaaS", "Impact tech", "Supply chain / Procurement", "Construction"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": true, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.85, "culture_fit_score": 0.72, "constraints": [{"id": "2c722f78", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Requires fully remote working; has been fully remote since 2019 and advocates strongly for it", "canonical_key": "remote_ok", "value": true, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98}, {"id": "9940d8ff", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Fully remote requirement; max 0 days in office", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": 0.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98}, {"id": "3bf9666b", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "ethics", "description": "Strong preference for B-corp certified companies or clear certification pathway; stated as a significant consideration and deep-level value", "canonical_key": "bcorp_required", "value": true, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88}, {"id": "a11fa004", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "ethics", "description": "Deeply committed to ethical, sustainable business practices; cares about company's position on sustainability and certification pathways", "canonical_key": null, "value": "sustainability-focused employer", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.92}, {"id": "233ab1dd", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "culture", "description": "Thrives in mission-driven environments; cares deeply about the purpose behind the work", "canonical_key": null, "value": "mission-driven, purpose-led organisations", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.93}, {"id": "c23bf55d", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "industry_background", "description": "Track record and expressed interest in B2B SaaS with sustainability or procurement domain relevance", "canonical_key": "industry_background", "value": "B2B SaaS, sustainability, or supply chain/procurement", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85}]}, "embedding": [-0.025409452617168427, -0.01109527051448822, 0.06380848586559296, -0.00329190562479198, 0.02172052301466465, -0.0009809843031689525, -0.009343385696411133, 0.0593646839261055, 0.007619986776262522, 0.005333990789949894, 0.029126865789294243, -0.030793292447924614, 0.0015008525224402547, -0.032958224415779114, 0.030821779742836952, 0.0642072930932045, -0.024910947307944298, -0.016721243038773537, -0.01363764051347971, 0.004262207541614771, 0.03842752426862717, 0.08528688549995422, -0.011657867580652237, 0.02699042111635208, 0.02408485673367977, -0.022632073611021042, -0.022133570164442062, 0.06813835352659225, -0.017917651683092117, -0.023785753175616264, 0.03537952899932861, -0.03261639177799225, -0.03216061741113663, 0.0007433047867380083, 0.001436759252101183, 0.0023002391681075096, 0.008709574118256569, 0.02150687947869301, 0.022019626572728157, -0.01556756254285574, -0.008275163359940052, 0.03255942091345787, 0.03908269852399826, -0.018202511593699455, -0.019669536501169205, -0.003938180394470692, -0.02922656759619713, 0.010881626047194004, 0.03854146599769592, 0.03404068946838379, 0.011843026615679264, -0.057085808366537094, 0.02774529904127121, 0.027830755338072777, 0.0012391380732879043, -0.0032295926939696074, 0.042102210223674774, -0.0025459302123636007, -0.012498202733695507, 0.022617829963564873, 0.00962824560701847, -0.035578928887844086, 0.017988866195082664, 0.042614955455064774, -0.012234708294272423, 0.009094133973121643, -0.01373734138906002, 0.000280185864539817, -0.00410909578204155, 0.02143566496670246, 0.042985271662473